**Thread Model:** A dedicated native worker thread handles all GPU processing off the main thread. Use a lock-free ring buffer for frame delivery with a separate render thread. The JavaScript thread only receives frame metadata and callbacks, never raw pixel data.

**Backpressure:** Implement a frame budget system (max 30fps output). Drop frames gracefully when the processing queue exceeds the threshold. Use event-driven notification rather than polling.

