Use a FlatList with a ref to scroll programmatically, track isAtBottom via onScroll, and auto-scroll to the end when new messages arrive only if isAtBottom is true. If the user has scrolled up, display a floating 'New messages' button that scrolls to bottom on tap. Use React.memo on message items and a stable keyExtractor to minimize re-renders. Set getItemLayout for fixed-height items to avoid measurement overhead.

## Minimal API
```
messages: Message[]
renderItem: ({ item }) => React.ReactElement
keyExtractor: (item) => string
```

## Implementation
```javascript
const ChatViewport = ({ messages, renderItem, keyExtractor }) => {
  const flatListRef = useRef(null);
  const [isAtBottom, setIsAtBottom] = useState(true);
  const [showNewMessages, setShowNewMessages] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (isAtBottom && messages.length > 0) {
      flatListRef.current?.scrollToEnd({ animated: true });
    } else if (messages.length > 0) {
      setShowNewMessages(true);
    }
  }, [messages.length, isAtBottom]);

  const handleScroll = ({ nativeEvent }) => {
    const { contentOffset, contentSize, layoutMeasurement } = nativeEvent;
    const atBottom = contentOffset.y + layoutMeasurement.height >= contentSize.height - 50;
    setIsAtBottom(atBottom);
    setShowNewMessages(!atBottom);
  };

  return (
    <View style={{ flex: 1 }}>
      <FlatList
        ref={flatListRef}
        data={messages}
        renderItem={renderItem}
        keyExtractor={keyExtractor}
        onScroll={handleScroll}
        scrollEventThrottle={16}
      />
      {showNewMessages && (
        <TouchableOpacity
          style={styles.fab}
          onPress={() => flatListRef.current?.scrollToEnd({ animated: true })}
        >
          <Text>New messages</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
      )}
    </View>
  );
};
```

## Testing Notes
- **Unit test**: Verify scrollToEnd is called when isAtBottom is true and new messages arrive
- **Unit test**: Verify button appears when scrolled up and hides after tap
- **Integration test**: Simulate scrolling behavior with Jest + React Native Testing Library
- **Memory**: Ensure FlatList properly recycles offscreen views

