## Thread Priority

The native audio thread must run at the highest scheduler priority. On iOS, this means Core Audio's real-time thread priority; on Android, use AAudio's AAUDIO_PERFORMANCE_MODE_LOW_LATENCY with SCHED_FIFO. Never block or allocate memory on this thread—use pre-allocated buffers exclusively.

## Buffer Management

A lock-free ring buffer decouples the real-time audio thread from the JS bridge thread. Write pointer advances only on the audio thread; read pointer advances only on the JS thread. Use atomic operations or memory barriers to ensure visibility without locks. Double-buffering with 128–256 frames provides 2.7–5.3 ms at 48 kHz, leaving margin for bridge latency.

## Power Considerations

Real-time audio is CPU-intensive. Optimize by using hardware DSP when available, scaling buffer sizes dynamically during silence periods, and implementing thermal throttling detection to gracefully reduce quality rather than glitch.

