## Why This Is Asked
Tests cross-language bridge design, real-time processing, and memory/power considerations for on-device ML in React Native.

## Key Concepts
- TurboModule/JSI bridge for synchronous, high-performance native access
- TensorFlow Lite integration in C++ for efficient on-device inference
- Lock-free ring buffers for zero-copy audio data transfer
- Dedicated worker thread architecture to avoid blocking the main thread
- Backpressure handling via configurable buffer limits and frame dropping
- Lifecycle management for clean resource teardown
- Privacy guarantees through fully on-device processing

## Code Example
```java
// NoiseSuppressorModule.java (TurboModule)
public class NoiseSuppressorModule extends TurboModule {
    private @Nullable Interpreter tfliteInterpreter;
    private @Nullable Thread audioWorker;
    private volatile boolean isProcessing = false;
    private final RingBuffer audioBuffer;
    private float suppressionStrength = 0.5f;

    @ReactMethod
    public void initModel(ReadableMap config, Promise promise) {
        try {
            String modelPath = config.getString("modelPath");
            tfliteInterpreter = new Interpreter(loadModelFromAssets(modelPath));
            promise.resolve(null);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            promise.reject("INIT_ERROR", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    @ReactMethod
    public void startStream(ReadableMap config, Promise promise) {
        if (isProcessing) {
            promise.reject("ALREADY_RUNNING", "Stream already active");
            return;
        }
        isProcessing = true;
        audioWorker = new Thread(() -> {
            android.media.AudioRecord record = createAudioRecord(config);
            record.startRecording();
            short[] buffer = new short[FRAME_SIZE];
            while (isProcessing) {
                int read = record.read(buffer, 0, FRAME_SIZE);
                if (read > 0) {
                    float[] input = preprocess(buffer, read);
                    float[] output = runInference(input);
                    short[] denoised = postprocess(output);
                    sendDenoisedFrame(denoised);
                }
            }
            record.stop();
            record.release();
        });
        audioWorker.setPriority(Thread.MAX_PRIORITY);
        audioWorker.start();
        promise.resolve(null);
    }

    @ReactMethod
    public void setStrength(double value) {
        suppressionStrength = (float) Math.max(0.0, Math.min(1.0, value));
    }

    @ReactMethod
    public void stop(Promise promise) {
        isProcessing = false;
        if (audioWorker != null) {
            audioWorker.interrupt();
            try { audioWorker.join(1000); } catch (InterruptedException ignored) {}
        }
        promise.resolve(null);
    }

    private float[] runInference(float[] input) {
        float[][] output = new float[1][input.length];
        tfliteInterpreter.run(input, output);
        return output[0];
    }

    private void sendDenoisedFrame(short[] frame) {
        WritableMap event = Arguments.createMap();
        event.putArray("data", createShortArray(frame));
        sendEvent("onDenoisedFrame", event);
    }

    @Override
    public void invalidate() {
        isProcessing = false;
        if (tfliteInterpreter != null) {
            tfliteInterpreter.close();
            tfliteInterpreter = null;
        }
    }
}
```

## Architecture Diagram

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        JS Thread                                 │
│  initModel() ─ startStream() ─ setStrength() ─ stop()           │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │ TurboModule/JSI
┌────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      Native Module (C++/Java)                    │
│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌───────────────────┐  │
│  │ TensorFlow   │◄───│  Inference    │◄───│ Lock-Free Ring    │  │
│  │ Lite Model   │───►│   Engine     │───►│     Buffer        │  │
│  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └─────────┬─────────┘  │
│                                                    │            │
│  ┌──────────────────┐                              │            │
│  │ Dedicated Worker │◄─────────────────────────────┘            │
│  │ Thread (MAX PRI) │                                             │
│  └────────┬─────────┘                                             │
│           │                                                        │
│           ▼                                                        │
│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │              Audio Hardware (Mic → Denoised)                │  │
│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

## Critical Considerations

1. **Latency**: Lock-free ring buffer eliminates mutex contention; MAX_PRIORITY thread ensures scheduling predictability.

2. **Backpressure**: Buffer depth limit (default 10 frames); oldest frames dropped when full; caller notified via event.

3. **Memory**: Single interpreter instance reused; pre-allocated buffers sized to max expected frame count; model loaded once at init.

4. **Privacy**: Zero network calls; all processing occurs on-device; no audio data leaves the device.

5. **Lifecycle**: NativeModule `invalidate()` guarantees cleanup on JS context destruction; stop() handles graceful termination.

## Usage Example
```javascript
